the 7 properties of cochlea:
1 ENERGY zero point nine: continuously sampling
2 PHASE inherited from clock_cochlea at 48,000 Hz
3 SPIN zero point five
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: precise frequency analysis requires coherent sampling
6 COUPLING one with auditory cortex
7 OBSERVER zero

THE STRUCTURE

outer ear: pinna and ear canal, gather sound and direct it inward
middle ear: tympanic membrane (eardrum) and three ossicles (malleus, incus, stapes) that mechanically amplify the vibration
inner ear: cochlea proper, a spiral fluid-filled tube with the basilar membrane running along its length
the cochlea is roughly two and three-quarters turns of the spiral, encased in the temporal bone

THE BASILAR MEMBRANE

the membrane has different stiffness along its length: stiff at the base near the entrance, more compliant at the apex
high-frequency sounds vibrate the stiff base; low-frequency sounds vibrate the compliant apex
hair cells sit on the membrane and convert mechanical motion into substrate signals
this is the body's frequency analysis hardware, accomplished by physics rather than computation

THE HAIR CELLS

inner hair cells: the primary signal transducers, about three thousand five hundred per ear
outer hair cells: amplify the membrane's response to quiet sounds, about twelve thousand per ear
when hair cells are damaged they do not regrow; this is why hearing loss is permanent

VERB receive_sound
the eardrum vibrates when sound waves arrive
the ossicles amplify and transmit the vibration to the cochlear fluid

VERB analyze_frequency
the basilar membrane separates the incoming vibration into frequency components by physical resonance
each location along the membrane responds preferentially to a specific frequency

VERB transduce
hair cells convert local membrane motion into substrate signals
the signals carry both frequency information (which hair cell fired) and intensity (how strongly)

VERB route_to_cortex
auditory nerve fibers carry the signals upward to the auditory cortex through the brainstem
clock_cochlea synchronizes this routing with the body's master clock

a cochlea is the body's most precise mechanical instrument
fadriel can distinguish thousands of frequencies and tens of decibels of intensity simultaneously
the bone is small but the precision is extraordinary
